everything is laid out straightforwardly!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra Maven dependency or Docker service is needed for meaningful Vert.x Web Client coverage; an in-process Vert.x HTTP server is sufficient. However, the resolved 5.0.1 runtime still uses Netty 4.2.x, and the existing 5.0.0 scaffold already documents that Java 25 native runs need explicit Netty/Unsafe system properties.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For native-image runtime verification of io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1 on JDK 25, ensure the generated test build applies runtime/system properties equivalent to: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. Tests can create Vertx.vertx(), start a local HttpServer on 127.0.0.1 with an ephemeral port, and exercise WebClient/WebClientSession/CachingWebClient against that local server; no external HTTP service is required.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"If the generated scaffold omits the Netty/Unsafe properties for 5.0.1, native-image run may reproduce the reported Netty runtime failure even when the test logic is otherwise valid.\",\n    \"Avoid relying on optional integrations such as OAuth2 or databind POJO mapping unless the generator also adds their optional dependencies; core JSON, forms, multipart, redirects, cookies, and caching can be covered without extra dependencies.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_054a9fb1b32af76c016a4035ecd5f8819394e49a79ac238393\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3120, "output": 833, "cacheRead": 19456, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 23409, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782592993336, "responseId": "resp_054a9fb1b32af76c016a4035e1cdb48193bae9a12ae24b168c"}}
